title: UAP unveils OBRA: A new identity for PH’s premiere architecture award
description: THE United Architects of the Philippines (UAP) formally unveiled OBRA, the new title and identity of the UAP Design Excellence Awards 2026 during its upcoming media launch and agreement signing with Davies Paints Philippines, the exclusive program partner of the awards.The event brought together UAP leaders, Davies Paints executives, media partners and representatives from the architectural community as UAP introduced the refreshed identity of its flagship awards program.OBRA represents the organization’s highest honor for architects and their built work. As the foremost recognition program of UAP, OBRA was established to promote outstanding architectural design and highlight projects that demonstrate purpose, relevance and vision. The new identity reinforces architecture as an authored act rooted in intention, clarity and cultural expression.Historically used in the Philippines to mean a work of art, the term “obra” reflects the creative and enduring impact of built environments on communities and national development.During the launch, UAP and Davies Paints Philippines reaffirmed their shared commitment to elevating design standards, strengthening public awareness of architecture and supporting the profession through meaningful collaboration.As part of the 2026 cycle, the registration period will run from Dec. 1, 2025 to Feb. 27, 2026, marking the formal opening of submissions. Shortlisted entries will be exhibited during the UAP National Convention in April 2026. The cycle will culminate with the OBRA Gala and Awarding Ceremony in May 2026, where UAP will present its highest distinctions for built work.
